    Ann Rheum Dis
    Distinct stromal and immune cell interactions shape the pathogenesis of rheumatoid and psoriatic arthritis.
Using receptor-ligand interactions and downstream target characterisation, we identify RA-specific synovial T cell-derived transforming growth factor (TGF)-ß and macrophage interleukin (IL)-1ß synergy in driving the transcriptional profile of FAPa + THY1 + invasive synovial fibroblasts, expanded in RA compared with PsA. In vitro characterisation of patient with RA synovial fibroblasts showed metabolic switch to glycolysis, increased adhesion intercellular adhesion molecules 1 expression and IL-6 secretion in response to combined TGF-ß and IL-1ß treatment. Disrupting specific immune and stromal cell interactions offers novel opportunities for targeted therapeutic intervention in RA and PsA.
